			<section id="Introduction" class="main-section">
				<header>
				<h2>Introduction</h2>
			</header>
				<p>This is a HTML documentation that discuses HTML and it's elements.It's Purpose is to make understanding and coding with HTML easier</p>
			
				<p>HTML is known as Hyper Text Markup Language.It is used in responsive web design to create fuctional web designs.</p>
			</section>
			<section id="Structure_of_a_HTML_Document" class="main-section">
			<header>
				<h2>Structure of a HTML Document</h2>
			</header>	
					<p>The Structer of a HTML document is fixed and it has a common syntax.A HTML document should include the following:</p>
							
					<ol>
						<li>html elemnt tag<code><html></html></code>.</li>
						<li>Head element tag<code><head></head></code>.</li>
						<li>body element tag<code><body></body></code>.</li>
					</ol>
				<p>This is a basic HTML boilerplate of it's skeletal structure</p>
			</section>
			<section id="HTML_Elements" class="main-section">
			<header>
				<h2>HTML Elements</h2>
			</header>
				<p>The HTML language has numerous elelments that are used in the different parts of it's structure.We'll name but a few:</p>
					<ol>
						<li><strong>Meta</strong><code>&lt;meta/&gt;</code> a self closing tag used in the head part for adding vital information like character and managing the viewport.</li>
						<li><strong>Title</strong><code>&lt;title&gt;&lt;/title&gt;</code>Used in the head part of the element for the title.</li>
						<li><strong>Link</strong><code>&lt;link/&gt;</code> Used in the head to link the hTML document to the styling sheet</li>
					</ol>
				<p>Next we'll discuss the elements used in the body.</p>
					<ol>
						<li><strong>header</strong><code>&lt;head&gt;&lt;/head&gt;</code>this usually holds the h1 and nav elements</li>
						<li><strong>main</strong> <code>&lt;main&gt;&lt;main&gt;</code> this is the main part of the document and all elememts go here.</li>
						<li><strong>footer</strong><code>&lt;footer&gt;&lt;/footer&gt;</code>this usually comes at the bottom of the page and holds final details</li>
					</ol>
			</section>
			<section id="More_Elements" class="main-section">
			<header>
				<h2>More Elements</h2>
			</header>
				<p>HTML has many more elements.Most will go into the main part of the document.</p>
				<ol>
					<li><strong>P</strong>(<code>&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</code>)It's used to write Sentences or paragraphs.</li>
					<li><strong>h1,h2,h3</strong>(<code>&lt;h1&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;</code>)This are used to write respective headings.</li>
					<li><strong>img</strong>(<code>&lt;img/&gt;</code>)Used to add images.</li>
					<li><strong>div</strong>(<code>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</code>)used to create special containers for styling</li>
					<li><strong>section</strong>(<code>&lt;section&gt;&lt;/section&gt;</code>)similar to div elements but are used for related blocks of content</li>
					<li><strong>form</strong>(<code>&lt;form&gt;&lt;/form&gt;</code>)used to create forms in HTML</li>
					<li><strong>Label</strong>(<code>&lt;label&gt;&lt;/label&gt;</code>)used to add labels to input elements</li>
				</ol>
				<p>That is to name a few.</p>
			</section>
			<section id="Attributes" class="main-section">
				<header>
					<h2>Attributes</h2>
				</header>
				<p>HMTL also has attributes. This are used together with html elements to improve functionality.They include:</p>
				<ol>
					<li><strong>alt</strong>(Used with with the img elements to provide an alternative)</li>
					<li><strong>src</strong>(Used with the img element to provide image source link)</li>
					<li><strong>href</strong>(Used to give the link being used)</li>
					<li><strong>radio</strong>(Used in the input element to make radio buttons)</li>
					<li><strong>action</strong>(shows where form is submitted)</li>
					<li><strong>method</strong>(shows how a form is submitted)</li>
				</ol>
			
				<p> That is the basic HTML structer with it's commonly used elements and attributes</p>
			</section>
		</section>
	</main>
